to the ongoing reimagining of English church history in the years prior to the Reformation. Surveying chronicle accounts, pamphlets, plays, poems, historical fictions, works of historical scholarship, civic pageants and monuments, films, and television programs, the book shows how an extended sequence of authors have told widely varying stories about Wolsey's life, often through the lens of their own religious and ideological commitments and/or in response to the pressing concerns of their times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCardinalszEnglandvBiography. 0aPrime ministerszEnglandvBiography. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071028140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823282203zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823282203423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823282203.jpg  a978-3-11-071028-1  NYUP / FUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK